* The heater on the Uponor has built in overheat-protection. If its to hot, then it turns off, and the power needs to be turned off for a while for it to restart. 
  Catch the situation where heat is not rising over a period of heating-moments and turn the power off for X minutes for it to restart.

* Fully support arguments,

* Make it possible to change desired temp from tcp/ip port.  (To make a mobile app for it later,)
